rlSmartPorts.name: rlSmartPorts
rlSmartPorts.description: The private MIB module definition for Smart Ports - provide a convenient way to save and share common configurations. Smart Ports group a group of command to be applied on a port or a trunk OR on a global configuration context. In addition Smart port application provide a database per interface (or global configuration) to list applied macros. Each smart port macro can either a user-defined or pre-defined.

rlSmartPortsMacroManageTable.name: rlSmartPortsMacroManageTable
rlSmartPortsMacroManageTable.description: The table listing available smart ports macros, holding: macro name macro type: user defined, Dell provided per interface Dell provided globally and matches a macro index to be used as identifier in rlSmartPortsMacroContentTable where the macro content really IS Allow to add/remove user defined macros.

rlSmartPortsMacroIndex.name: rlSmartPortsMacroIndex
rlSmartPortsMacroIndex.description: This variable identifies the macro's index. An arbitrary incremental Index used as identifier in rlSmartPortsMacroContentTable where the macro content really IS.

rlSmartPortsMacroType.name: rlSmartPortsMacroType
rlSmartPortsMacroType.description: This variable identifies the macro type: user defined, Dell provided per interface Dell provided globally

rlSmartPortsMacroContentTable.name: rlSmartPortsMacroContentTable
rlSmartPortsMacroContentTable.description: The table holds smart ports macro's content. Entries are allowed to be added ONLY on macro indexes that 1) has a corresponding entry in rlSmartPortsMacroManageTable 2) has rlSmartPortsMacroType = rlSmartPortsMacroUserCreated

rlSmartPortsMacroOctetIndex.description: This variable identifies the line number in the macro's content text. To allow full macro size of 3k = 19 * 160 = 3040

rlSmartPortsMacroDescriptionTable.description: The table holds smart ports macro's name globally (rlSmartPortsMacroDescriptionIndex == 0) interface (port or trunk).

rlSmartPortsMacroDescriptionIndex.description: This variable identifies global configuration when equals 0 OR local port or trunk on which the user saved Macro's name.

rlSmartPortsMacroDescriptionStatus.name: rlSmartPortsMacroDescriptionStatus
rlSmartPortsMacroDescriptionStatus.description: The status of a table entry. It is used to delete/Add an entry from this table.

rlSmartPortsFreeIndexes.name: rlSmartPortsFreeIndexes
rlSmartPortsFreeIndexes.description: Returns free index to set in rlSmartPortsMacroIndex when macro is added.

rlSmartPortsCondenseMode.description: disabled - in macro description macro such as x no_x will be removed enabled - in macro description macro such as x no_x will not be removed when condense mode is enabled (by default) each time a macro with the name no_x is applied and prior to that a macro x was applied , they will be removed from the list...
